OL,3,CLord Hague vows to champion 'free
OL,4,Cspeech' as he becomes university's
OL,5,CChancellor
OL,7,FLord William Hague vowed to champion
OL,8,Ffree speech and warned against
OL,9,F"comfort blankets of cancellation" as
OL,10,Fhe was officially admitted as the
OL,11,F160th Chancellor of the University of
OL,12,FOxford.
OL,14,FDuring his formal admission ceremony,
OL,15,Fthe former Conservative leader said
OL,16,Ffreedom of speech and of academic work
OL,17,Fand research "will be of paramount
OL,18,Fimportance" in an age where ideas
OL,19,Fchange rapidly.
