OL,3,CLord Hague vows to champion 'free
OL,4,Cspeech' as he becomes university's
OL,5,CChancellor
OL,7,FIn his speech, he said: "We cannot
OL,8,Fprepare for the turbulent decades to
OL,9,Fcome by shielding ourselves from
OL,10,Finconvenient arguments, wrapping
OL,11,Fourselves in comfort blankets of
OL,12,Fcancellation, or suppressing minority
OL,13,Fviews because they conflict with the
OL,14,Fbeguiling certainty of a majority."
OL,16,FLord Hague added: "Our university is a
OL,17,Fplace where we can disagree vigorously
OL,18,Fwhile sheltering each other from the
OL,19,Fabuse and hatred that are so often a
OL,20,Fsubstitute for rational opinion."
